b>: habitational name from farms named with <i>ny</i> ‘new’ + <i>mark</i> ‘field’.","Americanized form of German and Jewish (Ashkenazic)   Neumark  ."]},{"name":"Anglo-Norman Families","meanings":["Norman, English: locative name from any of the places in Normandy, Picardy, and Artois named (Le)  <i>Quesnay</i> or  <i>Quesnoy</i>, or elsewhere in N France named ( <i>Le</i> or  <i>La</i>)  <i>Chesnay</i> or  <i>Chesnoy</i>. The Domesday Book under-tenant came from Le Quesnay in Seine-Maritime (see   Anglo-Norman Families  ). The place-names all derive from Old French  <i>chesnai</i> or its Normanno-Picard equivalent  <i>quesnai</i> ‘oak grove’ (Medieval Latin  <i>casnetum</i>)."]},{"name":"Newmarsh","meanings":["Norman:  see  Newmarch  ."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Newmarche was born about 1142, in Womersley, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Sir Newmarche. She had at least 2 sons with Adam De Babthorpe."},"et":{"about 1142–":"umbes 1142–Surnud","1142–Female":"1142–Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1310":"1310","1142":"1142","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","about 1142":"umbes 1142","ABT 1160":"umbes 1160","Womersley, Yorkshire, England":"Womersley, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Babthorpe, Selby, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Selby, North Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","BABTHORPE, YORKSHIRE, ENGLAND":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1142–":"noin 1142–Kuollut","1142–Female":"1142–Kuollut","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1310":"1310","1142":"1142","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","about 1142":"noin 1142","ABT 1160":"noin 1160","Womersley, Yorkshire, England":"Womersley, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Babthorpe, Selby, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Selby, North Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","BABTHORPE, YORKSHIRE, ENGLAND":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1142–":"environ 1142–Décédée","1142–Female":"1142–Décédée","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","1160–Male":"1160–Décédé","1310–Male":"1310–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1310":"1310","1142":"1142","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","about 1142":"environ 1142","ABT 1160":"environ 1160","Womersley, Yorkshire, England":"Womersley, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Babthorpe, Selby, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Selby, North Yorkshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","BABTHORPE, YORKSHIRE, ENGLAND":"Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Margaret Newmarche est née environ 1142, à Womersley, Everwyck, Angleterre, 